* 5K Awards List — Race Roster unstructured upload
*
* Purpose:          Generates the printed awards listing AND uploads a single
*                   plain-text file (~awards-5k.txt) to Race Roster. Run after
*                   results are validated and before the awards ceremony.
*
* Race Roster setup (one-time, on raceroster.com):
*   1. Create a results race for this event (e.g. name it "Awards").
*   2. Set Result type to "Unstructured (Text/PDF)" — not Structured.
*   3. Copy the numeric results-race ID into Entries.INI as %rr_5k_awards_u%
*      (sample value: 283746). Distance and Display are optional for awards.
*   4. After upload, enable "Results are viewable by the public" to publish.
*   Race Roster displays the uploaded text as-is — same layout as awards-5k.txt
*   in this race folder (overall headers, age-group headers, finisher lines).
*
* Upload pattern (see docs: Publish Unstructured Results):
*   ONE destination file for all categories — not one file per age group.
*   RaceRosterHeader.rsm is the only sub-listing with External Report To,
*   Output Format txt, Destination, and the ##NNN## results-race ID marker.
*   OVERALL-RR.RSM and AGERES-RR.RSM use Destination Append to add each
*   section to the same ~awards-5k.txt file.
*   OVERHDR.RSM and EXCLUDE.RSM are print/processing only (no upload).
*
* IMPORTANT — ordering and append rules:
*   - RaceRosterHeader.RSM MUST be the very first RSM in this listing. It is the
*     only section that sets External Report To and registers the ##NNN##
*     sub-event ID, which the engine's upload gate requires. If it doesn't run
*     first, later sections are written to ~awards-5k.txt on disk but never
*     uploaded. Destination (not Append) also clears the previous run's file.
*   - Every subsequent RSM that produces upload output MUST use
*     Destination Append — never plain Destination. A plain Destination
*     would overwrite the file and destroy all sections written before it.
*   - RSMs that are print/processing only (OVERHDR.RSM, EXCLUDE.RSM) do not
*     have a Destination command at all — they execute but produce no file.
*
* Flow:
*   1. RaceRosterHeader.rsm -- Creates ~awards-5k.txt with ##%rr_5k_awards_u%##.
*   2. OVERHDR.RSM           -- Printed awards banner; resets exclude count.
*   3. @OVERALL-RR.RSM       -- Overall winners; appends to upload file; excludes.
*   4. AGERES-RR.RSM         -- Age-group winners; appends to upload file.
*   (FormFeedAtEnd.rsm is intentionally omitted — form feeds are irrelevant
*    for plain-text upload to Race Roster.)
*
* How to upload:
*   Right-click this listing → Send results to online.
*   Preview first with Output To Editor if desired.
*
* To customize:
*   - Change the first number in each line for winners per category.
*   - Add or remove AGERES-RR.RSM lines to change age group brackets.
*   - Keep "~awards-5k.txt" on every @OVERALL-RR and AGERES-RR line.
*
* See also:         Working example in every RunScore build:
*                   C:\RunScore\SampleRaces\5k\@awards2RR.6.R.lst
*
RaceRosterHeader.RSM %rr_5k_awards_u% "~awards-5k.txt"
OVERHDR.RSM
* Overall male and female awards (top 3 each)
@OVERALL-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F "~awards-5k.txt"
@OVERALL-RR.RSM 3 MALE   M "~awards-5k.txt"
* Age group awards (top 3 each, overall winners excluded)
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F 1  19 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 MALE   M 1  19 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F 20 29 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 MALE   M 20 29 "~awards-5k.txt"

AGERES-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F 30 39 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 MALE   M 30 39 "~awards-5k.txt"

AGERES-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F 40 49 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 MALE   M 40 49 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F 50 59 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 MALE   M 50 59 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F 60 99 "~awards-5k.txt"
AGERES-RR.RSM 3 MALE   M 60 99 "~awards-5k.txt"
